# Deployment Conventions

- Three compose services: `backend`, `frontend`, `redis`. Don't add new services without updating `PLAN.md` §13. Hosted production maps the same roles to Vercel (frontend), Render (backend Docker), and Upstash (Redis).
- The backend image bakes FAISS/BM25 indices and embedding weights at **build time** (`HF_HUB_OFFLINE=1` at runtime) so volume-less hosts (Render free tier) can serve traffic. Local Compose may still mount a named `faiss_index` volume; recreate it after changing `EMBEDDING_MODEL`.
- No production secrets baked into images — all config (API keys, tokens, thresholds) comes from environment variables documented in `.env.example`. A build-time `GOOGLE_API_KEY` placeholder is allowed only so ingest/index-build can construct Settings.
- Frontend image must read the backend URL from a runtime env var, not a build-time constant.
- Keep dependency-install layers separate from app-code layers in both Dockerfiles for build-cache efficiency.
- Any new required environment variable must be added to `.env.example` in the same change that introduces it.
- Next.js proxy routes must strip `Content-Encoding` / `Content-Length` / `Transfer-Encoding` when forwarding backend responses (Node `fetch` already decompresses gzip).
